----------------------------LINUX COMMAND LINE----------------------

/ -> root directory 
/bin -> for binaries 
/etc -> system configuration files 
/opt -> optional directories
/tmp ->temporaey space 
/usr -> user related programs 
/var -> log files / variables 
/dev -> device files,
/media -> media 
                                 
ls - list directory
cd - changes the current directory
pwd displays current working directory
cat concatenate or read files
echo - displays arguments to th screen
man - manual displays the online manual
exit - exit the shell 
clear - clears th screen
ls -l - long listing formatt
mkdir -p - canmake multiple directories inside each other
rmdir - deleting  a directory
chmod = changes the mode or permission of a user(u) groupg(g) or other (o)

